sep 21 1938

	...Lunch with Ambassador and Mrs. Kennedy....Talked with Ambassador Kennedy for an hour after lunch. We discussed the crisis and the aviation and general military situation in Europe. Everyone in embassy is extremely worried. Hitler is apparently ready to invade Czechoslovakia and has his divisions on the border. Hitler told Chamberalin [according to Kennedy] that he (Hitler) would risk a world war if necessary. Kennedy says England is ready to fight, even though not prepared. Chamberlain realizes the disastrous effects of war with Germany at this time and is making every effort to avoid one. English opinion (Kennedy) is pushing him toward war.





